<subSubSection id="C89655E1E3438056FF70FAC04752FAEC" pageId="8" pageNumber="1651" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8033066AE3438056FF70FAC04752FAEC" blockId="8.[178,1085,1312,1364]" pageId="8" pageNumber="1651">Etymology: The specific epithet is the superlative of the Latin adjective brevis (short) and alludes to the conpicuously small body size of the species.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C89655E1E3438054FF70FA84451EFE5B" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="1653" pageId="8" pageNumber="1651" type="description">
<paragraph id="8033066AE3438056FF70FA8447AFFA0C" blockId="8.[178,1085,1380,1460]" pageId="8" pageNumber="1651">
Description: Species of minute body size; body length 
<quantity id="4774AB8FE3438056FC94FA8447F6FAC2" box="[854,978,1380,1402]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.3" metricValueMax="4.5" metricValueMin="4.1" pageId="8" pageNumber="1651" unit="mm" value="4.3" valueMax="4.5" valueMin="4.1">4.1-4.5 mm</quantity>
; length of forebody 
<quantity id="4774AB8FE3438056FED4FA6145B4FA2F" box="[278,400,1409,1431]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.2" metricValueMax="2.3" metricValueMin="2.1" pageId="8" pageNumber="1651" unit="mm" value="2.2" valueMax="2.3" valueMin="2.1">2.1-2.3 mm</quantity>
. Habitus as in 
<figureCitation id="18B71AEFE3438056FDEFFA61465DFA2F" box="[557,633,1409,1431]" captionStart="Figs 19-24" captionStartId="9.[178,218,1445,1465]" captionTargetBox="[184,1067,574,1423]" captionTargetId="figure-168@9.[178,1085,574,1430]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 19-24: Lathrobium brevissimum: (19) habitus; (20) forebody; (21) male sternite VIII; (22) male sternite VII; (23-24) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view. Scale bars: 19-20: 1.0 mm; 21- 24: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5303207" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5303207/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="1651">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
. Coloration: body blackish-brown, with the posterior portion somewhat paler brown; legs and antennae pale-brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8033066AE3438057FF70FA2447B0FEB5" blockId="8.[178,1086,1476,1585]" lastBlockId="9.[178,1085,218,270]" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="1652" pageId="8" pageNumber="1651">
Head (
<figureCitation id="18B71AEFE3438056FF34FA244565FA62" box="[246,321,1476,1498]" captionStart="Figs 19-24" captionStartId="9.[178,218,1445,1465]" captionTargetBox="[184,1067,574,1423]" captionTargetId="figure-168@9.[178,1085,574,1430]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 19-24: Lathrobium brevissimum: (19) habitus; (20) forebody; (21) male sternite VIII; (22) male sternite VII; (23-24) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view. Scale bars: 19-20: 1.0 mm; 21- 24: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5303207" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5303207/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="1651">Fig. 20</figureCitation>
) 1.95-1.10 times as long as broad; punctation rather fine and sparse; interstices with distinct microreticulation, much broader than diameter of punctures. Eyes small and weakly projecting from lateral contours of head, composed of 12-15 ommatidia, and 0.20-0.25 times as long as postocular region in dorsal view. Antenna short, approximately 
<quantity id="4774AB8FE3428057FE85FF3A45B6FF48" box="[327,402,218,240]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="9" pageNumber="1652" unit="mm" value="1.3">1.3 mm</quantity>
long; antennomere II nearly twice as long as broad, III noticeably oblong, IV approximately as broad as long, and IV-X weakly transverse.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8033066AE3428057FF70FEFE4744FED6" blockId="9.[178,1085,285,366]" pageId="9" pageNumber="1652">
Pronotum (
<figureCitation id="18B71AEFE3428057FEE5FEFD4550FE8B" box="[295,372,285,307]" captionStart="Figs 19-24" captionStartId="9.[178,218,1445,1465]" captionTargetBox="[184,1067,574,1423]" captionTargetId="figure-168@9.[178,1085,574,1430]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 19-24: Lathrobium brevissimum: (19) habitus; (20) forebody; (21) male sternite VIII; (22) male sternite VII; (23-24) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view. Scale bars: 19-20: 1.0 mm; 21- 24: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5303207" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5303207/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="1652">Fig. 20</figureCitation>
) approximately 1.25 times as long as broad and 1.03-1.05 times as broad as head; lateral margins subparallel in dorsal view; punctation similar to that of head; impunctate midline broad; interstices without microsculpture.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8033066AE3428057FF70FE9D4571FE75" blockId="9.[178,1086,381,461]" pageId="9" pageNumber="1652">
Elytra (
<figureCitation id="18B71AEFE3428057FEC1FE9D4576FE2B" box="[259,338,381,403]" captionStart="Figs 19-24" captionStartId="9.[178,218,1445,1465]" captionTargetBox="[184,1067,574,1423]" captionTargetId="figure-168@9.[178,1085,574,1430]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 19-24: Lathrobium brevissimum: (19) habitus; (20) forebody; (21) male sternite VIII; (22) male sternite VII; (23-24) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view. Scale bars: 19-20: 1.0 mm; 21- 24: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5303207" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5303207/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="1652">Fig. 20</figureCitation>
) 0.56-0.57 times as long as pronotum, very weakly dilated posteriad; humeral angles weakly marked; punctation shallow, fine, and sparse. Hind wings completely reduced.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8033066AE3428057FF70FE3D47A6FD95" blockId="9.[178,1085,477,557]" pageId="9" pageNumber="1652">Abdomen 1.07-1.10 times as broad as elytra; punctation distinct and moderately dense, somewhat sparser on tergites VII and VIII than on tergites III-VI; interstices with distinct microsculpture; posterior margin of tergite VII without palisade fringe.</paragraph>
<caption id="D4F356E2E3428057FF70FA454505FA5E" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5303207" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5303207" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5303207/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="1652" startId="9.[178,218,1445,1465]" targetBox="[184,1067,574,1423]" targetPageId="9">
<paragraph id="8033066AE3428057FF70FA454505FA5E" blockId="9.[178,1085,1445,1510]" pageId="9" pageNumber="1652">
<emphasis id="B2F8DA78E3428057FF70FA45453DFA01" bold="true" box="[178,281,1445,1465]" pageId="9" pageNumber="1652">Figs 19-24</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName id="478C7DE9E3428057FEEAFA454634FA01" authorityName="Assing &amp; S" authorityYear="2013" box="[296,528,1445,1465]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lathrobium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="1652" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevissimum">
<emphasis id="B2F8DA78E3428057FEEAFA454634FA01" box="[296,528,1445,1465]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="1652">Lathrobium brevissimum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: (
<emphasis id="B2F8DA78E3428057FDE4FA454619FA01" bold="true" box="[550,573,1445,1465]" pageId="9" pageNumber="1652">19</emphasis>
) habitus; (
<emphasis id="B2F8DA78E3428057FD64FA454699FA01" bold="true" box="[678,701,1445,1465]" pageId="9" pageNumber="1652">20</emphasis>
) forebody; (
<emphasis id="B2F8DA78E3428057FCF5FA45476AFA01" bold="true" box="[823,846,1445,1465]" pageId="9" pageNumber="1652">21</emphasis>
) male sternite VIII; (
<emphasis id="B2F8DA78E3428057FBDDFA454012FA01" bold="true" box="[1055,1078,1445,1465]" pageId="9" pageNumber="1652">22</emphasis>
) male sternite VII; (
<emphasis id="B2F8DA78E3428057FEA6FA5B45BDFA77" bold="true" box="[356,409,1467,1487]" pageId="9" pageNumber="1652">23-24</emphasis>
) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view. Scale bars: 19-20: 1.0 mm; 21- 24: 0.2 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8033066AE3418054FF05FF3B46F7FE05" blockId="10.[178,1086,218,445]" pageId="10" pageNumber="1653">
: protarsomeres I-IV moderately dilated; tergite VIII oblong, not distinctly tapering posteriad, and with truncate posterior margin; sternite VII (
<figureCitation id="18B71AEFE3418054FCD3FF184778FEB6" box="[785,860,248,270]" captionStart="Figs 19-24" captionStartId="9.[178,218,1445,1465]" captionTargetBox="[184,1067,574,1423]" captionTargetId="figure-168@9.[178,1085,574,1430]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 19-24: Lathrobium brevissimum: (19) habitus; (20) forebody; (21) male sternite VIII; (22) male sternite VII; (23-24) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view. Scale bars: 19-20: 1.0 mm; 21- 24: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5303207" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5303207/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="1653">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
) distinctly transverse, with concave anterior margin and with weakly concave posterior margin, pubescence unmodified; sternite VIII (
<figureCitation id="18B71AEFE3418054FE7DFED2462CFEF0" box="[447,520,306,328]" captionStart="Figs 19-24" captionStartId="9.[178,218,1445,1465]" captionTargetBox="[184,1067,574,1423]" captionTargetId="figure-168@9.[178,1085,574,1430]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 19-24: Lathrobium brevissimum: (19) habitus; (20) forebody; (21) male sternite VIII; (22) male sternite VII; (23-24) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view. Scale bars: 19-20: 1.0 mm; 21- 24: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5303207" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5303207/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="1653">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
) weakly transverse, posterior excision moderately deep and moderately broad, pubescence unmodified; aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="18B71AEFE3418054FCD9FEAF47AAFEDD" box="[795,910,335,357]" captionStart="Figs 19-24" captionStartId="9.[178,218,1445,1465]" captionTargetBox="[184,1067,574,1423]" captionTargetId="figure-168@9.[178,1085,574,1430]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 19-24: Lathrobium brevissimum: (19) habitus; (20) forebody; (21) male sternite VIII; (22) male sternite VII; (23-24) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view. Scale bars: 19-20: 1.0 mm; 21- 24: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5303207" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5303207/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="1653">Figs 23-24</figureCitation>
) small, approximately 
<quantity id="4774AB8FE3418054FEC0FE8D4570FE3B" box="[258,340,365,387]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="1653" unit="mm" value="0.7">0.7 mm</quantity>
long, symmetric, and dorso-ventrally conspicuously flattened; ventral process basally broad and apically needle-shaped in ventral view; sclerotized dorsal plate absent; internal sac with dark membranous structures.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8033066AE3418054FF05FE2D451EFE5B" blockId="10.[199,314,461,483]" box="[199,314,461,483]" pageId="10" pageNumber="1653">: unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C89655E1E3418054FF70FE1246CCFD6D" pageId="10" pageNumber="1653" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8033066AE3418054FF70FE1246CCFD6D" blockId="10.[178,1086,498,725]" pageId="10" pageNumber="1653">
Comparative notes: Based on the external and male sexual characters, particularly the similarly modified aedeagus, 
<taxonomicName id="478C7DE9E3418054FD43FDF04738FD9D" authorityName="Assing &amp; S" authorityYear="2013" box="[641,796,527,549]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lathrobium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="1653" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevissimum">
<emphasis id="B2F8DA78E3418054FD43FDF04738FD9D" box="[641,796,527,549]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="1653">L. brevissimum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="478C7DE9E3418054FBEAFDF045E4FDFA" authority="ASSING 2012" authorityName="ASSING" authorityYear="2012" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lathrobium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="1653" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="planissimum">
<emphasis id="B2F8DA78E3418054FBEAFDF04516FDFA" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="1653">L. planissimum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="E41D7B9BE3418054FEFBFDCC45E4FDFA" author="ASSING V" box="[313,448,556,578]" pageId="10" pageNumber="1653" pagination="142 - 209" refId="ref6212" refString="ASSING V. (2012): A revision of the Lathrobium species of the Himalaya (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Paederinae). - Bonn Zoological Bulletin 61 (2): 142 - 209." type="journal article" year="2012">ASSING 2012</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(West 
<collectingCountry id="F89B46FAE3418054FDC9FDCC466FFDFA" box="[523,587,556,578]" name="Nepal" pageId="10" pageNumber="1653">Nepal</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion id="4248C888E3418054FD94FDCC473FFDFA" box="[598,795,556,578]" country="Nepal" name="Mahakali" pageId="10" pageNumber="1653">Mahakali Province</collectingRegion>
: Darchula District) of the 
<taxonomicName id="478C7DE9E3418054FBEAFDCE4528FDD8" authorityName="Coiffait" authorityYear="1982" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lathrobium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="1653" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jumlense">
<emphasis id="B2F8DA78E3418054FBEAFDCE4528FDD8" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="1653">L. jumlense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group. It differs from this species by the darker coloration, the more transverse male sternite VII, the deeper posterior excision of the more transverse male sternite VIII, and by the apically distinctly needle-shaped ventral process of the aedeagus. For illustrations of 
<taxonomicName id="478C7DE9E3418054FE21FD43465BFD00" authorityName="ASSING" authorityYear="2012" box="[483,639,674,696]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lathrobium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="1653" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="planissimum">
<emphasis id="B2F8DA78E3418054FE21FD43465BFD00" box="[483,639,674,696]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="1653">L. planissimum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and an explanation of characters shared by the species of the 
<taxonomicName id="478C7DE9E3418054FEA5FD2045F8FD6D" authorityName="Coiffait" authorityYear="1982" box="[359,476,703,725]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lathrobium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="1653" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jumlense">
<emphasis id="B2F8DA78E3418054FEA5FD2045F8FD6D" box="[359,476,703,725]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="1653">L. jumlense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group see 
<bibRefCitation id="E41D7B9BE3418054FD88FD5F46C7FD6D" author="ASSING V" box="[586,739,703,725]" pageId="10" pageNumber="1653" pagination="142 - 209" refId="ref6212" refString="ASSING V. (2012): A revision of the Lathrobium species of the Himalaya (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Paederinae). - Bonn Zoological Bulletin 61 (2): 142 - 209." type="journal article" year="2012">ASSING (2012)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C89655E1E3418054FF70FD044774FC8D" pageId="10" pageNumber="1653" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8033066AE3418054FF70FD044774FC8D" blockId="10.[178,1085,740,821]" pageId="10" pageNumber="1653">
Distribution and natural history: Thetypelocalityissituatedin Humla District (northwestern 
<collectingCountry id="F89B46FAE3418054FE26FCE14600FCAF" box="[484,548,769,791]" name="Nepal" pageId="10" pageNumber="1653">Nepal</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion id="4248C888E3418054FDEDFCE146C5FCAF" box="[559,737,769,791]" country="Nepal" name="Karnali" pageId="10" pageNumber="1653">Karnali Province</collectingRegion>
). The specimens were collected at the margins of snowfield at an altitude between 4250 and 
<quantity id="4774AB8FE3418054FD3FFCFF4768FC8D" box="[765,844,799,821]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.6" pageId="10" pageNumber="1653" unit="m" value="4600.0">4600 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
